# 1. First, log in to your server
#	- ssh root@server_ip_address
# 2. Create a new user account
#	- useradd username # once prompted, provide password
# 3. Add the user to the sudo group
#	- usermod -aG sudo username
# 4. Test
#	- su - username # Switch to newly created sudo user
#	- sudo whoami
# If the output of the whoami command returns root, then you have 
# successfully connected yourself as a new user
